Classes/Lobster.html#/s:7LobsterAAC23fet.name: fetchExpirationDuration
Classes/Lobster.html#/s:7LobsterAAC23fet.abstract: A fetch expiration duration. You can change it you want.

Classes/Lobster.html#/s:7LobsterAAC15use.name: useStaleChecker
Classes/Lobster.html#/s:7LobsterAAC15use.abstract: A flag indicating whether to check for stale status or not.

Classes/Lobster.html#/s:7LobsterAAC15sta.name: staleValueStore
Classes/Lobster.html#/s:7LobsterAAC15sta.abstract: A value store to store isStaled, which is the flag to judge remote config stale or not.

Classes/Lobster.html#/s:7LobsterAAC5fetc.name: fetch(completion:)
Classes/Lobster.html#/s:7LobsterAAC5fetc.abstract: Fetches config data from Firebase. If its cache hasn’t expired, RemoteConfig won’t fetch but will return cache data.

Classes/Lobster.html#/s:7LobsterAAC11set.name: setDefaults(_:)
Classes/Lobster.html#/s:7LobsterAAC11set.abstract: Set default config values. By setting default config values, You can use these value safely before fetching config data from Firebase.

Classes/Lobster.html#/s:7LobsterAAC11set.name: setDefaults(fromPlist:bundle:)
Classes/Lobster.html#/s:7LobsterAAC11set.abstract: Set default values using loaded data from plist

Classes/Lobster.html#/s:7LobsterAAC13cle.abstract: Clear default values and then RemoteConfig’s default values will be updated to empty.
